Articles.Content:
Hi! Having issues with KSP, I've owned the game for a long time, bought it when it was still early release, but too late for the free DLC. I've got almost 300hrs on Steam on it, plus some from separate modded installs. Haven't played it in a long time, and wanted to pick it back up but I can't get it running. I tried to start the old install up which had a lot of mods installed, but the updated Steam version was of course incompatible with all the mods. I cleared everything, installed a fresh install from Steam without any mods, but it still won't start up. I tried downgrading through many versions all the way down to 1.1.3, but none will start up. If I take the focus away from KSP, i.e. click another window after starting KSP from Steam, it will start up normally and get to the menu. As soon as I move the mouse over the window or change the focus to KSP, it crashes. If I start up normally with focus on KSP, it crashes while loading. 

OS: Win 10 Pro 1903 64bit
CPU: AMD Ryzen 7 2700X Eight-Core Processor  (16)
RAM: 16331
GPU: NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1070 Ti (8080MB)

Any idea what could cause this?

A user on the other thread with the same problem has posted a solution, closing MSI Afterburner 4.6.0.14820. There is some bad interaction between KSP and MSI Afterburner causing KSP to crash. No other games has shown any issues like this, so seems to be isolated to KSP. Hopefully this will help the devs to check if there's something they can fix, or of the problem is with Afterburner and will have to be fixed by MSI.
